# Spec-Kit & PRD Context

## Golden Source

For **001 ETL Configurator**, the authoritative product requirements are in:

`.specify/specs/001-etl-configurator/001-ETL-PRD.md`

## When Specifying or Clarifying

- Reference `001-ETL-PRD.md` when running `/speckit.specify` or `/speckit.clarify`
- Do not omit FR-*, GR-*, SC-*, EC-*, or constraint sections from the PRD
- User stories in `spec.md` should trace to PRD sections (journeys, functional requirements, guardrails)

## Document Roles

| Document | Use |
|----------|-----|
| `001-ETL-PRD.md` | Full product requirements – golden source |
| `spec.md` | Derived spec – user stories, acceptance scenarios |
| `data-model.md` | Target schema summary |
| `PRD.md` | Platform index; links to golden sources |
| `AGENTS.md` | Agent guidance |

## Avoiding Context Loss

When creating requirements from the PRD, ensure coverage of:
- All 8 core user journeys
- All functional requirements (FR-1.1 through FR-11.2)
- All guardrails (GR-1.1 through GR-10.4)
- Edge cases and constraints sections
- Success criteria and interaction model
